The paper discusses the evaluation of multi-label classifiers in supervised learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The datasets used in the evaluation are related to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR), and the paper discusses the need for explanations when a classifier performs worse than a baseline, which is also relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL).
